YR3l7fBA','He’d be waiting at the front door for me.\n“Fix the sink, Gus,” my grandmother would call out.\n“Can’t do, Emma,” Gus would call back.\n“Keith and I are going for a walk.”\nHe’d wink at me\nand whistle for Mr. Thompson Wooft,\nand our adventure would begin.','FgKKEwXfBmaSMgwn9HcwaWytpvzR',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3050,122,'FipWXraiJAlODch2Q7SCHkwrRj7g','We’d walk for miles.\nWe’d walk through towns,\nand we’d walk through the countryside...\nand Gus, he would hum every step of the way.\nHe’d hum whole symphonies\nas we strolled from on village to the next.\nHe’d hum funny little tunes\nas we wandered skinny streets and smoky alleys,\nmarching songs as we tiptoed around foggy ponds\nand explored silent forests.\nWith Gus, you had no idea where you’d end up.','FlRxhOhJcxr9fOEZalHSPWsZnL-F',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3051,122,'FgAJ2yJyV3Aj93lxTuQEjOf2BUMj','One time he led me all the way\nto the top of Primrose Hill\nto look at the night stars.\n“Don’t know if we can make it home tonight,”Gus said.\nSo we slept under a tree on the top of the hill,\nwith the sky lights above us and the city lights below.','FgsjcDCBAVuVwk9Yi1Rvaq1KVb27',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3052,122,'FqtGhWDqqSON7xn0PIqfHvOMrwSD','Once Gus walked us all the way to London and into the workshop of a big store that sold instruments.\n“Let’s just pop in here,\nI’ve got to pick up some strings.”\n“Okay, Gus.”','FgzRNBFaRmvvUEdMv3nhLPTEu1xo',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3053,122,'Fjzt0R_jCTA1kbSqXFumTlhG4eeX','Inside, it looked like a beehive.\nGus lifted me up and sat me on a shelf\nso that I could see everything.\nViolins hung from the ceiling by wires.\nHorns clung to the walls.\nMen in long brown coats\nfixed broken instruments and built new ones.\nI watched as they bent over\ncellos, trombones, and trumpets.\nThey dabbed at the drums with glue\nand tapped at them with tiny hammers.','Fi-Wj0AyCFhfWZ637BFhc78J9Q28',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3054,122,'FiO0eyAdux8S1mUqEZticub6PQuI','Men tested the guitar strings:dinka-plink dinka-plink.\nAnd the drums:dok-dok fum-fum dok-fum.','Fq1DXyAmkdo_EevC2if6kDl2l9wY',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3055,122,'FsgOhn-2AYHLvfL9MBibnRuz1V-4','My eyes followed a line of guitars\nthat snaked around the room on a conveyor belt.\nAnd in the middle of everything,\nbig, bubbling buckets of glue went blub blub blub.\nIt was magic.\nI sat on that shelf, watching it all.\nAnd right then, right there,\nI fell in love with instruments.','FrI-YNQ5HZczF23EcBGafnzdDIPI',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3056,122,'FiLarPBM55Uz4bp24D2eEgm2yUZU','When Gus and I got back to his house that day,\nI took a long look at that guitar\nthat always sat on top of his piano.\nIt seemed more beautiful than ever.\nAll I wanted was to make the strings go dinka-plink-plink\nlike the men in the store.\nBut I couldn’t reach it.\n“When you’re tall enough,you can have a go,”Gus said.','FhYQadbJgAeyTfNKx_u7ZWv81U21',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3057,122,'Ft80TWWl1y_RIqFgkIUnFYvoYVco','Every time I visited Gus, I reached for that guitar.\nEven on my toes, I couldn’t touch it.\nOne day, I felt like I was tall enough to grab it,\nbut I didn’t even have to try.\nGus simply handed it to me.\n“All yours,” he said.','FpTZUToztzf3qyxAUVfJisKQ7Lzk',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3058,122,'FnJkMKbBjgvjvFS5WprxStfg5e1y','He sat with me, taught me how to\nhold it, strum it, and pluck a little.\n“When you learn how to play \'Malaguena,\'”\nhe told me,“you can play anything.”\nDinka-plink dinka-plink dinka-plink.\nAnd I practiced and I practiced on that beautiful guitar.','Fpy2EHrtFUO_-lPGOgmuz6RSp2h1',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3059,122,'FixmOBq4VExHKqUxP2Y6nzG0WBAe','One day, Gus heard me playing “Malaguena,”and he nodded.\nThen he said something I’ll never forget:\n“I think you’re getting the hang of it.”','Fo_odKnBMQQkh51XCuNQ8nKY93Cf',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3060,122,'Fka_2ZpPDo1zhQypIcZyItGCuGHO','After that,\nI took that guitar everywhere,\nI went to sleep with my arms wrapped around it.\nEven today, all these years later, I think of Gus.\nEvery time I walk onstage,every time I write a song,\nevery time I reach for a guitar and play a few dinka-plinks\nfor my own grandchildren,I say to myself.','FpgAtvraNrtlzvaV1lYy6qe91_Ya',0,'2017-12-26 10:55:38','2017-12-26 10:55:38'),(3061,121,'FlMKXt4T3Whj5vvVA4CepR8lwI9D','Missing Mommy\n--by Rebecca Cobb','Fgw4rm_YNhDiZ_Lo_y1Lc9cfW_QL',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3062,121,'Fs08zq5AgiY8RYEsH3CH9GERClTQ','Some time ago we said good-bye to Mommy.\nI am not sure where she has gone.','Fm_1JgnWBhZAtefjad48jIOqzYga',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3063,121,'FhgrR2lAvpr4YY09mqwztEBu-3vR','I have tried looking for her.\nI found lots of her things.\nShe must have forgotten to take them with her.','FssiF6Dp3nlzu-510PR0yRdBO8IV',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3064,121,'Fp4UQNExE70b3F8o2ZGeVKVShNyG','We have been leaving her flowers...\nI don’t know why she hasn’t taken them.','Fum3FpetolyUTtfe3mfExWbrngna',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3065,121,'Fu_flQXNX4PZd9YF2Kpo70zyc-U0','I feel so scared\nbecause I don’t think she is coming back.\nAnd then I feel angry\nbecause I really want her to come back.','FpREqyjNQFcSezxhzqI2A7DHMH7L',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3066,121,'Fu2Fhl7rNQodBvBGrsQVLgSdD4VL','I am worried that she left\nbecause I was naughty sometimes.\nThe other children have THEIR moms.\nIt’s not fair.','FjZy1iu0KADkY0bEU5e3U86dTLj9',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3067,121,'Flg3WlBn1tcEuGvASE0BHk_v5N_G','I ask Daddy when Mommy was coming back.\nDaddy gave me a hug\nand told me that Mommy had died.','Foz9A5fL5T86M5XAclF9yEj42NzH',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3068,121,'FmqAcS02pMEU8XTs6AvocTdj9698','He said that when someone has died\nthey cannot come back\nbecause their body doesn’t work anymore.','FjHl5E2zUFTwpaJe8Ya3YJSBhkEi',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3069,121,'FguYwDBHXM7NaiCO5kTLJD9Jt35s','Daddy say it was nothing I did\nthat made Mommy die.\nHe wishes she was here too, but we are still a family.','Fh9ACmbFizss0WB9Xvku_hJ82Tgm',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3070,121,'FsLcqupuzX1_8aIi1OCxjFqd4Rs9','I’m glad I have people to care for me.\nWe can talk about things we remember.\nTogether we look at pictures\nthat makes us laugh and cry.','Fpp0Dk1ylT-L_pBrOaGs0QCclPXa',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3071,121,'FksbY4oZQFUrmwgx9fPf5yxfHjff','And we help each other to try and do\nall the things Mommy used to help with.\nDaddy says I do them very well.','FsLtMdwPbc2bXLmOlwAbj84X0Lse',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3072,121,'Fh1hSymTdytY9qxpdMHKLovYxYqg','I really miss my mommy.','FtOudKe9nPDEaQMCr950JaTi7bEY',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3073,121,'FiIpbWRzfaUtW2PlfXTVLZtkkXdo','But I will always remember her.\nI know how special I was to my mommy\nand she will always be special to me.','Fo60DKGqVeiSOGVGvCKXCENcCTfH',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:15','2017-12-26 10:56:15'),(3074,120,'Fn5uZyfPi_SVbQ6UhS1ra8_VIwJS','Goo, Goo!\n--by Teddy Slater','FlcsCsamVVHvPSZGJ8VXWu3fCLZv',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:36','2017-12-26 10:56:36'),(3075,120,'FhU3NWmpJ5v_5G8FBGJLJ9Ss-Y28','Everyone thinks my brother is too cute for words.\n“Kitchy, kitchy, coo!” they say.\n“Ooh, he is so sweet!” they croon.\nBut all my brother says is, “Goo, goo!”\nHe is too little to talk.\nHe just opens up his googly eyes.\nThen he smiles his goofy grin and drools.','FrQl0NCK2g8Szlge5n-1ru477UsG',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:36','2017-12-26 10:56:36'),(3076,120,'FjBhDcrMjBT_zfC1u0Hxnj_zzoLQ','My brother’s room is like a zoo.\nHe has a moose, a goose, a raccoon,\na poodle, a baboon, and a big kangaroo.\nHe has an owl that says, “Hoot!” and a cow that says, “Moo!”\nEveryone gives him stuffed animals.','FkjOiB2zRFGSBy5CaSQiyWiusZMz',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:36','2017-12-26 10:56:36'),(3077,120,'FgDlOpHmuBlKofjPSXI2oL7FAuh8','But does my brother say thanks? Nope.\nHe just says, “Goo, goo!”\nThat is all he can say:\n“Goo, goo! Goo, goo!”\nMy brother likes my toys, too.\nI have a car that goes VROOM\nand a plane that goes ZOOM.\nI have a drum that goes BOOM! BOOM! BOOM!\nAnd I have a choo-choo train with a red caboose.','Fr9-7Hbv6y_G88MDxj__MyS50Cuo',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:36','2017-12-26 10:56:36'),(3078,120,'FhfrcrnWfYjMKrormNdOSgtxaX2h','My brother has just one tooth,\nso he only eats gooey foods.\n“Goo, goo!” he says when you give him a noodle.\nHe can’t even use a spoon!\nAfter lunch, his eyes get droopy.\nSometimes he even snoozes all afternoon.','FoI5SmpdwAYp_Z33k5KGObIHNPtq',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:36','2017-12-26 10:56:36'),(3079,120,'Fvhli7XwkBMauFFiQ8I-elFB_xep','But as soon as I come home from school,\nhe wakes up.\nThen he gives me that good old grin\nand we play and play!\nAt night, in the moonlight,\nI help Mom put on his booties.\nShe reads him fun books like Winnie the Pooh.\nAfter that, I toot my kazoo\nand sing “Yankee Doodle Dandy.”','Fqy43P54gwxIPwq4vVeaXnK22a0l',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:36','2017-12-26 10:56:36'),(3080,120,'FtseTCiVLPLSXTI91bOn5hJNRg9X','If he is not in the mood to sleep, my brother cries,\n“Boo, hoo! Boo, hoo!”\nMy parents try oodles of things to make him stop.\nBut I’m the only one who can.\nI scoot over to his crib, scoop him up,\nand give him a big smooch.\nAnd just like that,\nhe goes from “Boo, hoo!” to “Goo, goo!”','FjhwFlfRbsii7G2VBoukhc3RhBL6',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:36','2017-12-26 10:56:36'),(3081,120,'Fs4_cZJiwv6_p6Axtb-nuBe8vFjm','That’s the cool thing about the kid.\nI love him and he loves me, too!\nIf I could pick any brother,\nI would always choose him!','FkgLefk_U7rTdUZDwybeCC_UnAqI',0,'2017-12-26 10:56:36','2017-12-26