 eyes of their father.\nThey helped the emperor rule the kingdom\nand teach the people the ways of peace.','FsurE_LgAdLSKnhkCr8ZC9BC1k62',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3937,161,'FrTqNAF9OThXKatQhJf_kpfV9Owo','Even her three sisters were all older, \nbigger and stronger than she.\nThey were like three midnight moons \nin the eyes of their father.\nThey were the ones who brought food to his table.\nBut Djeow Seow was like a tiny star \nin the emperor’s sight.\nShe was not even allowed to bring \na grain of rice to the meal,\nso little was she thought of.\nIn fact she was so insignificant,\nthe emperor often forgot he had a fourth daughter at all.\nAnd so, Djeow Seow ate by herself.\nAnd she talked to herself.','FleEfg0wg5Uv7vM6ptMzFDdJFQwA',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3938,161,'Fr40GNUZ1Sn380sU1pJCA_NTCcEa','And she played  by herself, \nwhich was the loneliest thing of all.\nHer favorite toy was a kite of paper and sticks.\nEvery morning, when the wind came from the \neast past the rising sun,\nshe flew her kite.\nAnd every evening, when the wind went to \nthe west past the setting sun,\nShe flew the kite.\nHer toy was like a flower in the sky.\nAnd it was like a prayer in the wind.\nIn fact a monk who passed the palace daily \nmade up a poem about her kite.\nMy kite sails upward.\nMounting to the high heavens.\nMy soul goes on wings.\nBut then he was a monk, \nand given to such thoughts.\nAs for Princess Djeow Seow,\nShe thanked him each day for his prayer.\nThen she went back, flying her toy.','Fgh4JW2O2rYvTZAGFWUeQDyaoctt',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3939,161,'Fu3xMuXlpDZJcjd4skQxPHnrd9C3','But all was not peaceful in the kingdom,\nJust as the wind is not always peaceful.\nFor the wind can trouble the waters of a still pond.\nAnd there were evil men \nplotting against the emperor.\nThey crept up on him one day when he was alone\nwhen his four sons were away ruling\n in the furthermost parts ofthe kingdom\nand his three daughters were down in the garden.\nAnd only Princess Djeow Seow, \nso tiny she seemed part of the corner \nwhere she sat, saw what happened.\nThe evil men took the emperor to a tower\n in the middle of a wide,treeless plain.\nThe tower had only a single window,\nWith an iron bar across the center.\nThe plotters sealed the door with bricks and\nmortar once the emperor was inside.\nThen they rode back to the palace and\ndeclared the emperor was dead.\nWhen his sons and daughters heard this,\nThey all fled to a neighboring kingdom\n where they spent theirtime sobbing and sighing.\nBut they did nothing else all that day.\nAll except Djeow Seow.\nShe was so tiny, \nthe evil men did not see her at all.\nAnd so, she crept to the edge of \nthe wide, treeless plain.\nAnd there she built a hut of twigs and branches.','FncgPKwaSYPoILlEhH-7q6Jn2hGI',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3940,161,'FjMJIaBn65AyoRoZd6cvFaHXKsh8','Every day at dawn and again at dark,\nshe would walk across the plain to the tower.\nAnd there she would sail her stick-and-paper kite.\nTo the kite string she tied a tiny basket filled with rice and\n poppyseed cakes, \nwaterchestnuts and green tea.\nThe kite pulled the basket high,\n high in the air,\nup as high as the window in the tower.\nAnd, in this way,\nShe kept her father alive.\nSo they lived for many days, \nthe emperor in his tower\nand the princess in a hut near the edge of the plain.\nThe evil men ruled with their cruel, harsh ways,\nand the people of the country were very sad.','FgLjWgMcUWAPT72iei0UnKhD0f_k',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3941,161,'FvOUj2oDNyt25rL2sxeKW9gTsqRW','One day as the princess prepared \na basket of food for herfather,\nThe old monk passed by her hut.\nShe smiled at him, \nbut he seemed not to see her.\nYet as he passed, \nhe repeated his prayer in a loud voice.\nHe said:\nMy kite sails upward.\nMounting to the high heavens.\nMy emperor goes on wings.\nThe princess started to thank him.\nBut then she stopped.\nSomething was different.\nThe words were not quite right.\n“Stop,” she called to the monk.\nBut he had already passed by.\nHe was a monk, after all, and did \nnot take part in things of this world.\nAnd then Djeow Seow understood.\nThe monk was telling her something important.\nShe understood.','FiFxLgflWIifOgwSjDTy8-Yysmzd',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3942,161,'FqOBCjQW6FRlOEdyAcQfBoalhfV1','Each day after that,\nWhen she was not bringing food to her father,\nDjeow Seow was busy.\nShe twined a string of grass and vines,\nand wove in strands of her own long hair.\nWhen her rope was as thick as her waist and\nAs high as tower, she was ready.\nShe attached the rope to the \nstring of the stick-and-paper kite,\nand made her way across the treeless plain.\nWhen she reached the tower,\nshe called to her father.\nBut her voice was as tiny as she,\nAnd her words were lost in the wind.','FnMuS6mwifUR2PM_3YtX3Jmy1JiQ',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3943,161,'Fj9Lmw1_UcV-m2MtKRPRBEPg9e_M','At last, though, the emperor looked out\n and saw his daughter flying the kite.\nHe expected the tiny basket of food \nto sail up to his window\nas it had done each day.\nBut what should he see but the \nstrand of vines and grass and long black hair.\nThe wind was raging above, \nholding the kite in its steely grip.\nAnd the princess was below, \nholding tight to the end of the rope.\nAlthough the emperor had never understood \nthe worth ofhis tiniest daughter before, \nhe did now.\nAnd he promised himself that if her plan worked \nshe would never again want for anything, \nthough all she had ever wanted was love.\nThen he leaned father out of the tower room and\nloosened the string of the kite.\nHe set the kite free, saying, \n“Go to thy home in the sky, Great kite”\nAnd the kite flew off toward the heavens.','FtPNxFCCipqkKmGN2bZNPH8GtA6K',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3944,161,'FiFus8AY9SfJ0gVTnDcfAUJt6k-U','Then the emperor tied one end of the thick \nstrand to the heavy iron bar\nacross the window,\nand the other and stretched all the way down\n to the Djeow Seow’s tiny hands.\nThe emperor stepped to the window sill,\nslipped under the iron bar,\nsaluted the gods,\nand slid down the rope.\nHis robes billowed out around him\n like the wings of a bright kite.','FkoM6cW1dkrizwdCJ4QBrh7cobz3',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3945,161,'FlI7vOC4fN1tDbg1JzIuIoD1i6cg','When his feet reached the ground,\nHe knelt before his tiny daughter.\nAnd he touched the ground before her with his lips.\nThen he rose and embraced her,\nand she almost disappeared in his arms','Fo8rlG3LP-mSh1elk9xMFXG0GRs0',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3946,161,'Fn-PxzUTMblTtXbWzTQtj2lQgAYN','With his arm encircling her,\nthe emperor said,\n“Come to thy home with me, loyal child.”\nHe lifted the tiny princess to his shoulders\nand carried her all the way back to the palace.','FrOjEmfI6IZmqpc4yV01YlqykP9W',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3947,161,'FgNHKObGnSCimScLK5boxGVzmLz5','At the palace,\nthe emperor was greeted by wild and cheering crowds.\nThe people were tired of the evil men,\nBut they had been afraid to act.\nWith the emperor once again to guide them,\nthey threw the plotters into prison.','FgotXJO9nkrPCBZj-fsemXJ5oNJY',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3948,161,'FouNkBRvlRtU_-np1atIJkEr-OID','And when the other sons and daughters \nof the emperor heard of his return,\nThey left off their sobbing and sighing,\nand they hurried home to welcome their father.\nBut when they arrived,\nThey were surprised to find Djeow Seow\nOn a tiny throne by their father’s side.\nTo the end of his day,\nthe emperor ruled with Princess Djeow Seow close by.\nShe never wanted for anything, especially love.\nAnd the emperor never again neglected a person-\nwhether great or small.\nAnd, too, it is said that Djeow Seow ruled after him,\nas gentle as the wind and,\nin her loyalty, as unyielding.\n,\n（本公众号文章欢迎转发，拒绝盗图或者转载！图片及译文仅供免费学习，如需完整绘本请支持原版）','FkLzGS66tiezh1QiW7bAz34AEONi',0,'2017-12-29 04:29:49','2017-12-29 04:29:49'),(3965,162,'FlhTPApD8aDs42DUbg41Vp6yT_Q4','Porcupine Pete\n--by Maria Fleming','Fs6Edrbik0lTvvKXZKMhsJ2U-v_W',0,'2017-12-29 04:46:34','2017-12-29 04:46:34'),(3966,162,'FuUofLBkt_uun15Hzs9rk13YamUA','My name is Rose.\nThese are my friends Luke, Jane, and Steve.\n“Do you want to ride bikes, Rose?”\n“Sorry, Jane. I can’t ride bikes today.”\nThese are my other friends Dave, Mike and Eve.\n“Do you want to get an ice cream cone?”\n“Nope. I need to get home.”','FgNvKopnSs6oTf23aLBIAyPfIK8O',0,'2017-12-29 04:46:34','2017-12-29 04:46:34'),(3967,162,'Fu_YHyxs58K2uRwD5Igzo6x_TnMr','They are good friends.\nBut my very best friend is my pet, Pete.\nPete and I do every thing together.\n“Pete!”\nPete is a great athlete.\nWe love to compete.\n“Watch out for that centipede, Pete!”\n“I hope I don’t fall on the concrete.”\n“Hey, I’m not a centipede. I’m a millipede!”','FihZ2PXbvk62FI-evYP-8oETtqGp',0,'2017-12-29 04:46:34','2017-12-29 04:46:34'),(3968,162,'Ftz3f_vBkjmw7PwXEO8FDpQikl1_','I spin Pete on the merry-go-round.\nIt tickles his spines.\n“I love spending time with you!”\n“What a fun ride!”\nWe like to sit side-by-side on a double-wide slide.\nDown we glide!\n“Let’s slide down twice!”\n“That would be quite nice!”','FjLUwEZ4xc6GNiyb5zbvzztJShEW',0,'2017-12-29 04:46:34','2017-12-29 04:46:34'),(3969,162,'Fq_-eLkGbo3ICC9E5CVz2B14zasB','Pete and I play hopscotch together.\nI hope to hop as well as Pete one day.\n“Those stones are no good.\nI need a small stone.”\nWe love to pose in silly clothes.\nIn a robe, I’m a queen on a throne.\nPete’s a clown in a cone hat and funny nose.\n“I love the clothes you chose!”','FvbLb9EfEO1SL7MdJocuqLa1slQ-',0,'2017-12-29 04:46:34','2017-12-29 04:46:34'),(3970,162,'FkDxU30u-85PETmOIcgeUumXy9iS','Sometimes we dress in a cap and cape.\nWe pretend we are brave superheroes.\n“I’m Blaze. What’s your superhero name, Pete?”\n“I’m Ace. I fly faster than a plane.”\nPete and I make fake cakes for picnics by the lake.\n“Wow! He ate it all.”\n“Yup! He cleaned his plate.”\n“No, Pete! Just pretend to eat it.”\n“But it tastes yummy. I didn’t want to waste it.”','Fr8kgvqhfmIrGUaybP7jXYwYPRuR',0,'2017-12-29 04:46:34','2017-12-29 04:46:34'),(3971,162,'FtlJH_uQ-_bbN1gge1uAW3C2ThMx','It can be tricky to give Pete a hug.\nBut it’s not a huge problem.\n “I refuse to give up hugs.”\n“I’m a huge fan of hugs.”\nWe just use marshmallows!','Fr5SZno5tRFJDezqiJmMBnw9GJqY',0,'2017-12-29 04:46:34','2017-12-29 04:46:34'),(3972,162,'Fj24Z04Mr5eeyfeNOAYeFD7mNEKK','Pete is always by my side.\nLife would not be complete without my pet, Pete!\n“Pete, I would not trade you for anything \nin the whole wide world.”\n“Me, neither.”','Fj5gb1sQM4c_A5cE13PkVJF1kL1y',0,'2017-12-29 04:46:34','2017-12-29 04:46:34'),(3973,163,'Fm6em57nUhcFNudCGjEb40-Yiyag','First words bath time\nBy Mustard\n2，Bathtub','FiV6ibs3PyltlondR7PY60ONsB_5',0,'2017-12-29 04:49:49','2017-12-29 04:49:49'),(3974,163,'FvFTijwNY1ONNSh8U-flNX3bE5Jg','Faucet','FjqQX9Hlhxu4z7qF8UlzzUt40p_p',0,'2017-12-29 04:49:49','2017-12-29 04:49:49'),(3975,163,'FmSF7WSyy1POmUFnCtpVFKc3RHA_','Duck','Fn7NofDqB18ZlXqOhJeUCNtdoHUL',0,'2017-12-29 04:49:49','2017-12-29 04:49:49'),(3976,163,'FjjxoTPNc6c1fNllajxFjBRIYJ6f','Shampoo','FqchTYd8rHuMM5QsmNSqXTOnv5Mz',0,'2017-12-29 04:49:49','2017-12-29 04:49:49'),(3977,163,'FmJTd8sAcan81MQl1YmGij1rgMdl','Sponge','Ftch-MhhX_C_o9uZvgoCB5wbAbWs',0,'2017-12-29 04:49:49','2017-12-29 04:49:49'),(3978,163,'FkQ-tfEkWmSoJ53DKwhe_op7yMJv','Bubbles','FmNR0jI5Tkap3uy_FFVm2Gdl1Ei0',0,'2017-12-29 04:49:49','2017-12-29 04:49:49'),(3979,163,'FpcPbHRJpT6nbjzjLqNTIZ85AeNm','Boat','FtkEIzAl2fooLT9SLL083sN3eY8l',0,'2017-12-29 04:49:49','2017-12-29 04:49:49'),(4029,150,'FolpqB1ybGq9Qq7x7Vyz7EWQKREL','Fryderyk Chopin','Fv3br6Y_cSBxePxT6gBG8GfEf3RF',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4030,150,'Fg5w9WF50cH7kV-GqzPgZksqHdXk','The winter was hard in Poland in the year 1810.\nInspite of the blanket of snow,\ndrums and violins can be heard quite clearly\n below the windows of a fine red-roofed house near Warsaw:\nsome street musicians have come to celebrate\nthe birth of a son into the new Chopin family.\nIn his cradle, little Fryderyk starts to cry with fright.\nTo comfort him, his mother hums a sweet, sad song.','FpFRa-_R38YM7CCjkMRMHJVadTlU',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4031,150,'Fi98vsrwWsAxrifZE6CaS5kiRJqy','Mr. Chopin is French and is a French teacher.\nHe wants his son to speak several languages.\nSoon Fryderyk is learning Latin, Greek , \nFrench, and then German, English and Italian!\nBut the one he likes best of all is the language of music.\nHis mother first introduces him to the piano\n and at just five years old, \nFryderyk makes up a little tune for his father’s birthday.','FpY_0x1PeJhJ9Ebhvm9pQ91qXPDv',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4032,150,'Fv0PfznR_HoIEYPKNmCd2D7tCEZG','Fryderyk was aprodigy at the piano,\nas if born with the notes already under his fingers.\nWhen he was eight he was invited to\nplay for the brother of the Russian Tsar,\nthe Grand Duke, a stern, temperamental man.\nFryderyk was nervous as he sat down at the piano,\nbut as soon as his fingers touched the keys\n the palace was full of beautiful sounds.\nHow proud his father was!','Fi3tMbPKMUzv55DwKn9U3XquhwNq',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4033,150,'FpiLunBVvsZdxBCGLCV00mCRig5p','As a boy,\n Fryderyk spent his summer holidays in the country.\nAt one harvest festival the villagers\ngot together and sang to the sound of violins.\nThe peasant girls, all wreathed in flowers,\ndanced and tapped their heels.\nFryderyk couldnot resist the rhythm of the music;\nhe grabbed hold of a bass viol \nand joined in with great enthusiasm.','FnrNCD10hTdDN9iixwZljx9Aqe98',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4034,150,'FrL7imbgd0L7hIrT8u2KM1O3jHVp','One evening when he was twelve,\nFryderyk’s father took him to the opera.\nFryderyk was entranced.\nWhat joy, drama and passion there was\n in the mixture of music and theatre!\nHow beautifully those voices rose above the orchestra!\nLater on he would make his piano sing\nas no-one had ever done before.','Fs1fbD26z68A7WcU6G3TlSFxhqPO',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4035,150,'Fkj96XAr4us234steiVX6CUPWw8-','One day, as he was coming out of church,\nhis eyes met those of a young girl of his own age.\nFryderyk fell hopelessly in love.\nHer name was Constance and she had a beautiful voice\nand dreamt of becoming a singer.\nBut Fryderyk was too shy to express his love,\nexcept through the piano, his trusted friend.','Fr0kd44Ajz-ZeVt_MKGQCiFUPEOF',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4036,150,'FrmXUeBukl_YhMVA9ITAX33FWNXd','By the time he was seventeen\nFryderyk Chopin had already played in many concerts.\nHe was by now a famous pianist and\nadmired as a composer in Poland.\nBut he wanted the world to hear his music.\nAt the age of twenty he decided he must leave Poland!\nAs the coach took him off on his travels,\nhis heart ached at the thought of those\n he was leaving behind…','FufvHHt9wx2ooyha0aAN2K4iv7-5',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4037,150,'FrIpiLbVF2QbfdIWOxqUmWiL-yXJ','Fryderyk moved to Paris.\nIn the studio of the painter Eugene Delacroix \nhe met George Sand, a famous woman writer.\nThey fell passionately in love.\nThe great musician was now the master of his art.\nHe was a success whenever he played\nand Paris showered him with praise.\nToday as in the past \nChopin’s music is played and loved.','FhU0CSfNYivCwnEZ9dqlX0i4b0I1',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4038,150,'FuAMgvijxNmILkSglpbWRefxrQLb','Music to learn by\nTHE STUDIES\nChopin had no more piano lessons\nafter the age of twelve.\nBut he devoted himself to this instrument\nthroughout his whole life.\nThis is very unusual in the history of music.\nAs soon as he came to Paris,\nChopin began to give lessons.\nPianists from all over the world became his pupils\nand he dedicated many of his compositions to them.\nHe was a brilliant pianist and a genius at improvisation.\nHis studies are extremely difficult to play\nand are terrifying tests of skill.\nBut they greatly widened the range of sound\nthat can be produced on the piano.\nBy composing his twenty-four studies,\nChopin truly helped create the modern piano.','Fp8FnLpLzXDyyDfXvVjOtLefBK9U',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4039,150,'FiMd0yz6_HgPxIVvqJn_DfZp-NcF','Music to dance to\nTHE MAZURKAS\nIn 1830 Chopin left Poland; He did not return.\nBut he never forgot the dance tunes\nhis mother played on the piano,\nnor the songsand dances of the village festivals.\nSo through music he was able to recall his native country.\nHe wrote polonaises - noble, heroic dances.\nHe also composed elegant, refined waltzes\n and more than fifty mazurkas.\nThese mazurkas are Chopin’s particular speciality.\nIn a three-time dance rhythm,\nthey reflect his longing and his changeable moods.\nSome are despairing, Others are joyful; Some are both.\nThe one you are about to hear combines sadness and joy.','FoQvuR7v8WZa_b6dRro3iI8KPHs9',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4040,150,'FtNOCG2UYiS5vH2-uUN_HjUqEwGF','Music to dream by\nNOCTURNES AND BALLADES\nChopin’s music reflects his dreams.\nThe piano is his mirror：\nall his sensitivity and his feelings are expressed through it.\nIn George Sand’s beautiful house in Nahant,\nChopin adored the romantic atmosphere at dusk\n and felt in harmony with the secret whisperings \nas daylight faded.\nIt was there that he composed his ballades and nocturnes.\nA ballade is like a poem for an instrument that tells a story.\nNocturnes are reveries-dreamy pieces-or musical loveletters.\nChopin used to say,\n‘ If you want to play the piano, you have to make it sing’.\nIn the following nocturne,\nlisten to how the music sings and breathes\n just like a human voice.\nYou can recognize Chopin’s music by this voice-like quality.','Fhcq1fNVcdT0loU-q-AYGxJ64JDE',0,'2018-01-02 09:43:36','2018-01-02 09:43:36'),(4062,166,'FqFIOV94W9CQnCMf305XSzvJeV5Q','Gus Makes a Gift--I Love Mom\n--by Frank Remkiewicz','FqVl3vIPMjl84oUeZ8DcctA0_Rbz',0,'2018-01-03 06:44:44','2018-01-03 06:44:44'),(4063,166,'FuyGBf-Gbf2gDzB147ByUksQIGRd','Gus goes to school.','FgkUWS6KEtrSF_6H27ZEzOOR9-AG',0,'2018-01-03 06:44:44','2018-01-03 06:44:44'),(4064,166,'FuKcASA3iOf7QGc0G6ahGkEBaKAg','“Bye, Dad.”\nGus loves school.','FraIdWbiHLzewIByNL4b5QbLpJbe',0,'2018-01-03 06:44:44','2018-01-03 06:44:44'),(4065,166,'FhZM_SgHHylgWjI6i0mYMBwZtgET','It is time for art.\nWhat will Gus make?','FmQZUKSC32RZ3hI6Ojtlk-3_jE-C',0,'2018-01-03 06:44:44','2018-01-03 06:44:44'),(4066,166,'Fvc0Su7QxqG-n0eHAIJygklstAGL','Gus makes a gift.\nMom will love it.','FhhaATZvOh8Ef3vVIMP3DmodBtMc',0,'2018-01-03 06:44:44','2018-01-03 06:44:44'),(4067,166,'FpMzpcOAFE-6_aZqzvWNUgWj2e_1','Here are some beads.\nGus likes beads.','FuB7Yqh4S01D6LwN1Uw_wzc4oxSz',0,'2018-01-03 06:44:44','2018-01-03 06:44:44'),(4068,166,'FrE5Un1G5-o7yRvwl6OeeVAVBdVt','Gus loves red beads.\nGus makes a gift.','FjxHKIjBWpT-a-GiRxfHjcEeiIkE',0,'2018-01-03 06:44:44','2018-01-03 06:44:44'),(4069,166,'FjTW6_JIMaBaTOMSCwl_yEnzaMpJ','“See my beads!” says Tess.\n“See MY beads!” says Gus.','FnFlA5NhnkOVSRoNqR1vUmg0SxLI',0,'2018-01-03 06:44:44','2018-01-03 06:44:44'),(4070,166,'Fh-4oxPG72vg1ncZnAnuSx0eexrl','“NOW see my beads!” says Tess.\n“Now see MY beads!” says Gus.','FsYsSUxkhqtK345NUh9_4PZ4i8hr',0,'2018-01-03 06:44:44','2018-01-03 06:44:44'),(4071,166,'FmuESORoHIKhwrjo-rnaQKeLDNJw','Oops!\nMom will still love it.','Fv7VLvkOQD1eMzu-FmqzXS6lAs76',0,'2018-01-03 06:44:44','2018-01-03 06:44:44'),(4072,166,'Fk0dTpCaYxwkG3wZTkxlH3Sj_l9h','Gus runs home.\nMom loves her gifts.','FrcZS8FwVAt4n7Po42fNNnA5654T',0,'2018-01-03 06:44:44','2018-01-03 06:44:44'),(4073,166,'FhpVuhOS4z6DJPR0tapMvKNa0