e of its corners he put an inscription:\nSometimes one must travel far\nto discover what is near.\nIsaac sent the captain of the guards a priceless ruby.\nAnd for the rest of his days he lived in contentment\nand he never was poor again.','FhMK2jPM3Q7W_71RWpBLKDc7haaS',0,'2018-01-05 08:30:15','2018-01-05 08:30:15'),(4156,142,'Fq3lMAp7v_Y9JSqOrbR0XCpu3yyS','Splat the Cat Sings Flat\n--by Rob Scotton','FioBoz7uG5RJNAJ9QuViyGsEu9lZ',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4157,142,'FrKCCXFIvN7F9SMH4AvP5dO0nUfn','Splat the cat goes to Cat School.\nSplat likes to take Seymour.\nSeymour is Splat’s pet mouse.\nSeymour rides in Splat’s hat.','FihsSwNtXOtUvTXsyXxcGnIhmH-r',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4158,142,'Fpcy2nygmE99ioHlLSFwCuFGk5qN','One morning, Splat’s teacher had big news.\nShe asked all the cats to sit on the big red mat.\nSeymour sat in Splat’s hat.\n“All of you will sing on Parents’ Night,”\nMrs. Wimpydimple said.\n“If your singing is loud, your parents will be proud.”','Fo0x7qAjxSiQW8wuVBR_wFcLYcpN',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4159,142,'Frel93t_bXbZPUFFTsxofzvZ1rfm','“Will lots of parents be there?” asked Splat\n“Yes. All the parents,” said Mrs. Wimpydimple.\n“Gulp!” said Splat.\nSplat’s tail wiggled wildly.\nSplat was worried. \nSplat was shy. ','FoEX5MPLXjdlnpD2IB2NuoI49qtA',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4160,142,'FjjumED2sZD03s8v_vtNTQjQQBcB','“I can’t sing,” said Splat.\n“Can you meow?” asked his teacher.\n“I forget how to meow,” said Splat.\n “Can you hum?” asked his teacher.\n“I even forget how to hum,” said Splat.','FmDVyrwFDF0eFrIMj016SeXsGJae',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4161,142,'FulV3lgftqRQ7vY0cFUKP-ni-_AB','“That’s okay, Splat,” said Mrs. Wimpydimple.\n“I will help you sing. We will all help you sing.”\nMrs. Wimpydimple sang first.\n“La-la-la!” she sang.\nThe cats on the mat began to sing.\nAll except Splat. ','FtiuNnc2soZevenHs_bi-8PdeYYe',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4162,142,'FiiV9FT1kGvz6EJfcnqgr77UJShf','“Now you try, Splat,” said Mrs. Wimpydimple.\nSplat opened his mouth. \nNothing came out.\n “You can do it, Splat,” said his teacher.\nSplat tried hard, but all that came out was a little squeak.','FnczWo7qAVjVgbmOyNpbhC5qsLQd',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4163,142,'FgEjhCGOllBAhR0Te80S6JR1Lftp','Splat looked at Seymour.\nSeymour was brave.\nHe was a mouse in a room full of cats.\nSplat could be brave, too. \nSplat opened his mouth again.\n“La!” sang Splat.\nThe note was loud.\nIt was long.\nAnd it was very, very flat!','Fs475UjsuJew1tVgdtYjX-2OvXz8',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4164,142,'FtenEJYR-koLNbgyIT0cKQ8w9otd','The cats on the mat went wild.\nSplat was not trying to be funny, \nbut he was funny anyway. \n “Sing just like that!” said Mrs. Wimpydimple.\n“You will be the star with a mouse in his hat!”\n“Maybe,” said Splat. ','FnDbrD_lNPdnROWX_4edKRdlBW8x',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4165,142,'FptCb-c7oNwhre5kxYwUaK0Elk0b','Splat went home after school.\n“What if I forget my part?”\nSplat asked Mom and Dad.\n“You won’t forget,” they said to Splat. \n “Maybe I will forget,” said Splat.','Fq1KWCDPSiIa_aZqoLyCGb2_gvMr',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4166,142,'FgWVOP5YpNeiTOqx5eYLeRqUmjY9','Splat put Seymour on his head.\nSplat’s tail wiggled and Seymour jiggled.\nSplat sang “la!” \nThe note still came out flat.\n“Maybe I won’t forget,” said Splat. ','FgOEl2uPiBMwrKvBdkW9ceHvQwJV',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4167,142,'FrUJh3u1kPAXFeUkkl7t1YnmqZ7I','Soon it was Parents’ Night.\nAll the parents came to Splat’s classroom.\nThe class stood on the big red mat. \n“Let’s begin!” said Mrs. Wimpydimple.\nThe class started to sing.\n“La-la-la!” sang the cats.\nBut Splat stayed quiet.\nHe waited for his turn. ','FndzU8d6ou2sZAnchT4iHxR-q9lU',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4168,142,'Fjb2iJeaRXZRfBRXfnET0VSyWznw','Mrs. Wimpydimple gave Splat a nod.\nSplat was ready.\nSeymour jumped onto Splat’s head.\nSeymour was ready, too.\nSplat’s tail wiggled wildly.\nSplat opened his mouth very wide.\n“La!” sang Splat, and the note was flat.\nIt was very flat and very loud.\nHe opened his mouth even wider.\n“LA!” sang Splat. \nThen he opened his mouth as wide as it could go. ','FkI7eniYRwxcF5UhgBFEjPBTwTbV',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4169,142,'FvFx8SKD4gSbv8mHUqp-7y8ENp-Z','“LAAA!” sang Splat, and he fell off the mat.\nSPLAT!\nThe class giggled.\nThe parents laughed.\nAnd Splat laughed the loudest of all. \nSPLAT!\n “You were the star!” said Splat’s mom. \n“We are very proud of you,” said Splat’s dad.','FsphYfXlkDMs_YtUX3RYFXJLQgDp',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4170,142,'FsUQ9q4--lblddmJJO_M1tc4oz6J','“Splat was the cat’s meow!” said Mrs. Wimpydimple.\nSplat was happy.\n“Guess what,” said Splat.\n“I didn’t forget to sing flat!”\nI forgot to be shy.','FpZatZ3LQ4JrFDyvHt6odf5QrtPF',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4171,142,'Fj3bAc8q0Xo8obe8hfyY7vbdZY-8','Mom and Dad hugged Splat.\n“We love our cat who sings flat.”','FmkdFJui1GYemK-780bfuz5e3U-D',0,'2018-01-08 03:16:41','2018-01-08 03:16:41'),(4174,173,'Fo8N7_uGOOhNZBWC4eV34The8kt1','Sylvester and the Magic Pebble\n-- by William Steige','FiUqQzb-ms0ZzGsHz7sf1OtOhHln',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4175,173,'Fs9rCccwRK8Z3xUtvWQ8jQ8N8qXs','Sylvester Duncan lived with his mother and father at Acorn Road in Oatsdale. One of his hobbies was collecting pebbles of unusual shape and color.\nSylvester  Duncan 和爸爸妈妈住在Oatsdale的Acorn 路，他的爱好之一是搜集各种不同寻常形状和颜色的鹅卵石。','FrgL5ewoegaYdkr8tSKtDJMZvcRE',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4176,173,'FpichC8exYNJgzwaGFmCvX9FYFdC','On a rainy Saturday during vacation he found a quite extraordinary one.It was flaming red, shiny,and perfectly round, like a marble. As he was studying this remarkable pebble, he began to shiver, probably from excitement,and the rain felt cold on his back.“I wish it would stop raining,” he said.\nTo his great surprise the rain stopped.It did’nt stop gradually as rains usually do.It CEASED. The drops vanished on the way down,the clouds disappeared, everything was dry,and the sun was shining as if rain had never existed.\n在一个假日的下雨的星期六，他发现了一块非常特别的鹅卵石。那是一个火红的，闪闪发光，圆溜溜的石头，就像弹珠一样。或许是因为太兴奋了，就在他仔细研究这块漂亮的鹅卵石的时候，他开始发抖，雨点落在背上也让他觉得很冷。“我希望雨停了。”他说。\n让他非常吃惊的是雨竟然停了。雨不是像平常那样逐渐的停了，而是突然停了。雨点还没落到地上就消失了，乌云也不见了，每一样东西都是干的，太阳出来了，好像从未下过雨一样。','FqZ2l2jpWQPWeosyrqs6NNfkUiNf',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4177,173,'FuMB5jGhDab-RTAeuObUytH4cYru','In all his young life Sylvester had never had a wish gratified so quickly.It struck him that magic must be at work,and he guessed that the magic must be in the remarkable-looking red pebble.(Where indeed it was.), To make a test, he put the pebble on the ground and said,“I wish it would rain again.” Nothing happended. But when he said the same thing holding the pebble in his hoof,the sky turned black, there was lightning and a clap of thunder,and the rain shooting down.\n“What a lucky day this is!”thought Sylvester. “From now on I can have anything I want.My father and mother can have anything they want.My relatives, my friends,and anybody at all can have everything anybody wants!”\nHe wished the sunshine back in the sky,and he wished a wart on his left hind fetlock would disappear,and it did, and he started home, eager to amaze his father and mother with his magic pebble.He could hardly wait to see their faces.Maybe they wouldn’t even believe him at first.\n在Sylvester之前的人生里，从没有如此快的实现一个愿望。他突然觉得一定是有魔法在起作用，而且他猜魔法一定是来自那个非常漂亮的红色的鹅卵石（事实上也是如此）。为了证实他的想法，他把石头放在地上，说：“我希望下雨。”然而并没有下雨。但是当他用蹄子拿着鹅卵石，并说同样的话的时候，天空变得黑了下来，并且出现了闪电和雷鸣，雨突然就下了起来。\n“今天是多么幸运的一天啊!” Sylvester想，“从现在开始，我想要什么就有什么，我的爸爸妈妈也可以想要什么就有什么，我的亲戚，朋友们，还有所有人都可以想要什么就有什么。”\n他希望太阳再次在天空出现，希望自己左后面蹄子上的疙瘩消失，这些愿望都实现了。接着，他准备回家了，急着要用这个神奇的石头让爸爸妈妈惊喜一下。他迫不及待地想看到他们的表情，也许爸爸妈妈起初根本不会相信他。','FvbtqrjAE5AlcQJ5cx5_qFwPkLWR',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4178,173,'Fnr1QQH1Yn3-jPfGj-ECog5XNtU8','As he was crossing Strawberry Hill, thinking of some of the many ,many things he could wish for, he was startled to see a mean,hungry lion looking right at him from behind some tall grass.He was frightened. If he hadn’t been so frightened,he could have made the lion disappear,or he could have wished himself safe at home with his father and mother.\nHe could have wished the lion would turn into a butterfly or a daisy or a gnat.He could have wished many things, but he panicked and couldn’t think carefully.\n“I wish I were a rock,” he said ,and he became a rock.\nThe lion came bounding over,sniffed the rock a hundred times,walked around and around it, and went away confused, perplexed,puzzled, and bewildered. “I saw that little donkey as clear as day. Maybe I am going crazy,” he muttered.\n就在他穿过草莓山，心里想着有很多很多的愿望要实现的时候，遇到了一只狮子。这只狡诈、饥饿的狮子在高高的草丛后面直直的看着他，他吓坏了。要是他没被吓坏的话，他就会想到让狮子消失，或者希望自己平安地和爸爸妈妈在家里。\n他本可以希望这只狮子变成蝴蝶，雏菊或者是虫子，他可以想到好多办法，但是他太害怕了，以至于他都没来及仔细的想。\n“我希望我变成石头。”他说，然后他就变成了一块石头。\n狮子跳了过来，在石头边闻了一遍又一遍，绕着石头走来走去，然后非常困惑的走开了。走的时候还自言自语：“我明明看见了那只小驴的，难道是我饿疯了吗？”','Fge5Q3-mkQ49X-TYbyYy503rpjcG',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4179,173,'FkKjvEyb90RhU2EO8lCzQsYTpAht','And there was Sylvester, a rock on Strawberry Hill,with the magic pebble lying \nright beside him on the ground,and he was unable to pick it up.“Oh, how I wish I were myself again,” he thought,but nothing happened. He had to be touching \nthe pebble to make the magic work,but there was nothing he could do about it.\nHis thoughts began to race like mad.He was scared and worried. Being helpless, he felt hopeless. He imagined all the possibilities,and eventually he realized that his only chance of becoming himself again was for someone to find the red pebble and to wish that the rock next to it would be a donkey.Someone would surely find the red pebble-it was so bright and shiny- but what on earth would make them wish that a rock were a donkey? The chance was one in a billion at best.\nSylvester fell asleep. What else could he do? Night came with many stars.\nSylvester就这样变成了草莓山上一块小石头，那块魔法石就在他的边上，但是他却不能捡起它。“哦，我多么希望变回我自己啊。”他想，但是根本没有用。他必须碰到魔法石才能产生法力，但是他现在什么都不能做。\n他开始有各种想法，他非常害怕和担心，无助并且很绝望。他想象了各种可能性，直到最后他意识到他能变回他自己唯一的机会是有人能发现那个红色的魔法石，并且希望红色石头旁边的那个石头能变成一头驴。当然了，一定有人会发现红色的魔法石，它是那么闪亮和耀眼，可是世界上谁会希望一个石头变成一头驴呢？这个机会顶多只有十亿分之一。\n最后，Sylvester睡着了。他不睡又能怎样呢？星星出来了，夜幕降临了。','Fu8AmWXR23O6lTdA7Tv1vBzwenlo',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4180,173,'Fm6utGZlpPU6HfZPXJ7C07Uk8Jrh','Meanwhile, back at home, Mr. and Mrs. Duncan paced the floor,frantic with worry.Sylvester had never come home later than dinner time. Where could he be?They stayed up all night wondering what had happened,expecting that Sylvester would surely turn up by morning. But he didn’t, of course. Mrs. Duncan cried a lot and Mr. Duncan did his best to soothe her.Both longed to have their dear son with them.\n“I will never scold Sylvester again as long as I live,”said Mrs. Duncan,“no matter what he does.”\nAt dawn, they went about inquiring of all the neighbors.\n与此同时，Duncan先生和太太在家里走来走去，担心得快要疯了。Sylvester从来没有在晚饭后回家，他去了哪儿呢？他们一晚没睡，都在想发生了什么，希望早上就能看到Sylvester。可是，Sylvester当然没有回家。Duncan太太哭得很伤心，Duncan先生尽量安慰她，他们都期望能和他们的宝贝儿子在一起。\n“今后，我再也不训斥Sylvester了。”Duncan太太说，“不管他做了什么。”\n清晨，他们就去向所有邻居们打听。','FozJcJP_LbuU-1D3Vz4m1dyhoER_',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4181,173,'Ful74l70Uqn5nvJvSrCfZz1G_ZmN','They talked to all the children—the puppies,the kittens, the colts, the piglets. No one had seen Sylvestersince the day before yesterday.They went to the police.The police could not find their child.\n他们问了所有的孩子们，小狗，小猫，小马和小猪。但是自前天起，就再也没人看见Sylvester了。他们还去找了警察，但是警察也说没有找到他们的孩子。','Fizn7VfXmx9PKjuU4EbeKM8KtiuW',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4182,173,'Fokg3E5GB0Q_mRgkq6GO3l5ZtmgD','All the dogs in Oatsdale went searching for him.They sniffed behind every rock and tree and blade of grass,into every nook and gully of the neighborhood and beyond,but found not a scent of him.They sniffed the rock on Strawberry Hill,but it smelled like a rock. It didn’t smell like Sylvester.\nOatsdale里所有的狗都出动寻找Sylvester，他们闻遍了每一块石头、每一棵树和每一片草叶的背面，找遍了远近的每一个角落和溪谷，都没有发现他的气味。他们也在草莓山上闻过那块石头，但是都是石头的味道，没有一点Sylvester的味道。','FhjjJcABnnbjiFh51fV_N_Ob5MbM',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4183,173,'FmUDNyfptWtYtNEggZpJZlxHKvqZ','After a month of searching the same places over and over again,and inquiring of the same animals over and over again, Mr. and Mrs. Duncan no longer knew what to do.They concluded that something dreadful must have happened and that they would probably never see their son again.(Though all the time he was less than a mile away.)\nThey tried their best to be happy,to go about their usual ways.But their usual ways included Sylvester and they were always reminded of him. They were miserable.Life had no meaning for them any more.\n经过一个月一遍又一遍的搜寻同样的地方，一遍又一遍的询问同样的动物们，Duncan夫妇再也不知道该做些什么了。他们认为一定发生了什么可怕的事情，他们可能再也见不到他们的儿子了。（虽然他一直都在离他们不到一英里的地方。）\n他们尽量高兴起来，就像他们以前一样。但是以前一直有Sylvester在，并且他们也一直会想起他，他们觉得很悲伤，生活对他们已经不再有意义了。','FrULwNudNDhDLy8yNWJNfcO-COYp',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4184,173,'FsR0_IDmoWu_B91BsXIMi3azJvaP','Night followed day and day followed night over and over again. Sylvester on the hill woke up less and less often. When he was awake, he was only hopeless and unhappy.He felt he would be a rock forever and he tried to get used to it,he went into an endless sleep. The days grew colder. Fall came with the leaves changing color.Then the leaves fell and the grass bent to the ground.\n多少个日日夜夜过去了，Sylvester在山上醒着的时候越来越少。当他醒来的时候，他只会觉得绝望和难过。他觉得他会永远变成一块石头。他努力的去习惯这件事，所以他一直在睡觉。天气变冷了，秋天来了，叶子都改变了颜色，叶子落了下来，草也垂到了地面上。','FmBgGWv11ZzIW8B_SMCQfZOYAINJ',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4185,173,'Fg8uPaFt2w2PxaT5v_Dc2F2pNt3q','Then it was winter. The winds blew, this way and that.It snowed. Mostly, the animals stayed indoors,living on the food they had stored up.\nOne day a wolf sat on the rock that was Sylvester and howled and howled because he was hungry.\n冬天来了，风从四面八方吹过来。下雪了，大部分的动物们都呆在家里，靠着之前他们储存的食物过冬。\n有一天，一只狼坐在Sylvester变成的那块大石头上，因为饥饿而不停地嚎叫。','FhpGL8FD09ZBJDtC76MnK4x3k0_6',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4186,173,'FkDGfBRsqdgjl_lRC87BmJfJNop9','Then the snows melted. The earth warmed up in the spring sun and things budded.\nLeaves were on the trees again.Flowers showed their young faces.\n然后，雪融化了，春天的阳光让大地变得暖和，树木花草都开始发芽了。\n树上又长出了叶子，花儿也开始开放了。','FkTuiNnI2GJmscXbwpaqtTMqgD-W',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4187,173,'FnkgnkkSZeB-xyxuPf6kKVhoQwHZ','One day in May, Mr. Duncan insisted that his wife go with him on a picnic.\n“Let’s cheer up,” he said.“let us try to live again and be happy even though Sylvester, our angle,is no longer with us.” They went to Strawberry Hill.\nMrs. Duncan sat down on the rock.The warmth of his own mother sitting on him woke Sylvester up from his deep winter sleep.How he wanted to shout, “Mother! Father!It’s me, Sylvester, I’m right here!”but he couldn’t talk. He had no voice.He was stone-dumb.\n五月的一天，Duncan先生坚持要他的妻子和他一起去野餐，“让我们振作起来”，他说，“让我们努力快乐的生活，即使我们的天使Sylvester不再和我们在一起。”于是，他们去了草莓山。\nDuncan太太坐在那块岩石上,妈妈的温度唤醒了冬眠的Sylvester。他多么想大声的叫：“妈妈！爸爸！是我，Sylvester，我在这儿！”但是他不能说话，他不能发出声音，就像一块石头一样不能说话。','Fox4pKAnkNMU1uRP1KBB0GeCYxBL',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4188,173,'FtfcNZMKn2foWf_cfXpUfy_hng_6','Mr. Duncan walked aimlessly about while Mrs. Duncan set out the picnic food \non the rock—alfalfa sandwiches,pickled oats, sassafras salad, timothy compote.\nSuddenly Mr. Duncan saw the red pebble.“what a fantastic pebble!” he exclaimed.“Sylvester would have loved it for his collection.”He put the pebble on the rock.\nThey sat down to eat. Sylvester was now as wide awake as a donkey that was a rock could possibly be.Mrs. Duncan felt some mysterious excitement.”You know, Father,” she said suddenly,“I have the strangest feeling that our dear Sylvester is still alive and not far away.”\n“I am, I am!” Sylvester wanted to shout, but he couldn’t. if only he had realized that the pebble resting on his back was the magic pebble!\nDuncan先生漫无目的的走着，Duncan太太把野餐准备的食物拿得到岩石上，有苜蓿三明治，燕麦，沙拉和果盘。突然，Duncan先生看到了红色的鹅卵石，“多么美妙的石头啊!”\n他感叹道，“Sylvester应该会很想收藏这个。”他把鹅卵石放在了岩石上。\n他们坐下来吃东西。这时候，Sylvester虽然是块石头，但是却像驴子一样完全清醒了。Duncan太太感觉到有些说不出的兴奋。“你知道吗，爸爸，”她突然说，“我有种奇怪的感觉，我们亲爱的Sylvester还活着并且就在不远处。”\n“我是，我是！”Sylvester想喊，但是他不能。要是他能知道那个在他背上那个石头就是那个魔法石，那该多好！','FgOP83xeK-q-6jK0QZLL7pPUWuVJ',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4189,173,'FgcCJ3ZARQycTaBXZU2gfEg2IrFH','“Oh, how I wish he were here with us on this lovely May day,”said Mrs.Duncan. Mr. Duncan looked sadly at the ground.“Don’t you wish it too, Father?” she said.He looked at her as if to say,”How can you ask such a question?”\nMr. and Mrs. Duncan looked at each other with great sorrow.\n“I wish I were myself again,I wish I were my real self again!”thought Sylvester.\n And in less than an instant, he was!\nYou can imagine the scene that followed—the embraces, the kisses,the questions, the answers, the loving looks, and the fond exclamations!\n“哦，在这美好的五月天，我多么希望他能和我们一起啊。”Duncan太太说。Duncan先生悲伤地看着地上。“你是不是也这样想，爸爸？”她说。Duncan先生看着她，那表情好像是在说：“你怎么能问这样的问题？”\nDuncan先生和太太悲伤地看着对方。\n“我希望我变回自己，我希望变回真正的我！”Sylvester想。\n然后一瞬间，他变回来了！\n接下来的场景你可以想得到，拥抱，亲吻，询问，回答，怜爱的眼神和欢喜的感叹。','FjB9fGaL_49swke0JwQGGZrGcS_g',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4190,173,'Frt0s7Pfl-W1usDUNd__mm8PG-Kd','When they had eventually calmed down a bit,and had gotten home,Mr. Duncan put the magic pebble in an iron safe.Some day they might want to use it, but really, for now,what more could they wish for?They all had all that they wanted.\n当他们逐渐平静一点的时候，他们回到了家里，Duncan先生把魔法石放到了铁的保险箱里。或许有一天他们会用它，但是，说真的，现在他们还有什么可期望的呢？因为他们已经得到了他们想要的一切。','Fj_lBjkVrMZdYYtmvKsFgqPClr9M',0,'2018-01-09 11:45:09','2018-01-09 11:45:09'),(4227,71,'FskN5xgG7jFTw64BEY6o5VyTnjHU','Jig has 1 wig.','Fjem-5bq5RLYsMWY7cB9uXBPi9OT',0,'2018-01-21 03:28:52','2018-01-21 03:28:52'),(4228,71,'FmciZg9Ns-hWzFwte3GfzcV18ByK','2 bugs in a rug. Pup has 3 cups.','Fj7T-l1-EWJia-E6cqSwyxSGGRk5',0,'2018-01-21 03:28:52','2018-01-21 03:28:52'),(4229,71,'FsVq5cnJgdsfnBOQO-BQG8HfTh37','Mac has 4 hats. Dot has 5 pots.','Fmpmt6EeRKWmf1MA6aQWU3Kfi3TJ',0,'2018-01-21 03:28:52','2018-01-21 03:28:52'),(4230,71,'FgNrGdVT-XHQRn6KDC1HtfPT7XiZ','Cat has 6 caps. Ruff has 7 pups.\nMag has 8 bags. Muff has 9 rags.','Fih8j94TyiixIfRtaTC50PJ1Da30',0,'2018-01-21 03:28:52','2018-01-21 03:28:52'),(4231,71,'Fh-nPwnQozqFjiq2vq8mzpHU7FB2','Dot has 10','FverhGaO37BhF1TkwI1cgLWJ2ayf',0,'2018-01-21 03:28:52','2018-01-21 03:28:52'),(4268,174,'Fh6vb4zS1brOs9Z-W1TL-YgD68vd','Red Fox and his Canoe','FnkCXCu9xTjjf78G5a0sc64NaIjY',0,'2018-01-23 06:11:58','2018-01-23 06:11:58'),(4269,174,'Fn_jgXQqkkw5dgTk6O2IpjvohNs5','So Al came along, too.\nAnd all three bears caught fish\nwhile Red Fox paddled\nHow could he get rid of the bears','Foh_9S-Unm2XvOVIfgc3DcmV5oe6',0,'2018-01-23 06:11:58','2018-01-23 06:11:58'),(4270,174,'FjbOyc51V5JWqvMbWDB1C2uVmAvt','Then Red Fox thought of a trick\nto get rid of the bears.\n“Hey, look here! \"he said \n“Look in the water!”\nAll the bears turned and looked\nand the canoe tipped way over.','FtOJrq06piipr8yJC-oo7pKTJ-nH',0,'2018-01-23 06:11:58','2018-01-23 06:11:58'),(4271,174,'FgVXcrgaSNIsn5vu5CLib0MazvhU','But before Red Fox could tip it all the way,\ntwo otters came aboard.\n“ Thank you,” said one otter.\n“We were getting tired of the water.”\n“it\'s lucky this is a big canoe,”\n said the other otter.\n“ We can do our fishing from here.”\n“ Go over that way.There are more fish there.”','FiqTXgKUUFTLH5c69LM6ypbw4sI-',0,'2018-01-23 06:11:58','2018-01-23 06:11:58'),(4272,174,'FnZ3OBqhsK2TGhp72ZX_5ix4_Jte','As they passed underneath the limb of a tree\na raccoon jumped into the canoe\n“Excuse me.” he said.\n“I want to wash a piece of meat.”','FgJi6W8cw7QZFV0dEyi0eg9Mwbg6',0,'2018-01-23 06:11:58','2018-01-23 06:11:58'),(4273,174,'Fs2uN0np5JG8KLzGZZ