tic!\n“My goodness!” said Mama.\n“We forgot the attic.”\nThey went up to the attic.','Fvb8xdGqI_LAdc27ooOYS6NOZV48',0,'2018-02-11 03:49:45','2018-02-11 03:49:45'),(4909,191,'FrXFL3YWqneWjwEmuh67cATr0-5S','It was bad.\n“My goodness!” said Mama.\n“There are too many things!”\n“Yes,” said Papa.\n“Many too many to put in the yard.”','Fl3MMkFoj0pqyrTLrmn_VDl1D-Im',0,'2018-02-11 03:49:45','2018-02-11 03:49:45'),(4910,191,'FjLB_GnZD6EKOcUJ5_CuDcvbD4Zl','They went downstairs.\nThey went out to the yard.\nThey made a sign.\nIt said YARD SALE TODAY.','Fky660fBSwomf2Vty4vrGwy-Z3YT',0,'2018-02-11 03:49:45','2018-02-11 03:49:45'),(4911,191,'FvZ6Q69KfpWIrH8cFtabxqqKRHkQ','They looked at the things they put in the yard.\n“This is hard,” said Papa.\n“I love those things I put in the yard.”\n“This is hard,” said Mama.\n“I love those things I put in the yard.”\n“This is hard,” said Brother and Sister.\n“We love the things we put in the yard.”','FjWEYz23aILXDuleNooKgAv2VhWp',0,'2018-02-11 03:49:45','2018-02-11 03:49:45'),(4912,191,'FtRycNZUjXpwZaxtR3-q2SwkABMD','They took them up to the attic.\nThey put them with the other old things they loved.','Fqa7udKPKFCfDyqSOKHDSJTtCu6Z',0,'2018-02-11 03:49:45','2018-02-11 03:49:45'),(4913,191,'FmD33ib1BmAcX8BITqEYDZqpu5cp','“We have done our job,” said Mama.\n“But we are not done,” said Brother.\n“We have not cleaned the attic,” said Sister.','FubfwXOwpcv6sK0ptInMmxWwg6L_',0,'2018-02-11 03:49:45','2018-02-11 03:49:45'),(4914,191,'FqxkzKKwO_Nu8wn1vmebFF_bZrsI','“We are done,” said Mama.\n“But the attic will not go away.\nWe will clean the attic another day.”','FvJXP7HdbC_XsCzHs__NIGWeY8ae',0,'2018-02-11 03:49:45','2018-02-11 03:49:45'),(4915,192,'Fr1VFAtMweI_Yx1OxqatP-Fw1yDZ','“But we have help- \nShep, our sheepdog, herds our sheep.”\n“I cover a lot of ground in my trusty Jeep.”\n“My scarecrow keeps the crows away,\nand, of course, farm machines are here to stay.”','FhC8XMS503CljOQTSVk49ycmVxCz',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4916,192,'FsWoTOpJuuLraQVlPGrURlaYITvU','“Our barn cat, Burt, keeps the mice away.”\n“As for milking - I still like to do it the old-fashioned way.”','Fnw4WIbiXBSBOSDsc2zxE8t2efYR',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4917,192,'FnuGX8y9rMZ-skTVX9BHb9NoaE2H','“Here, Brother Bear. Give it a try.”\nOops! Brother gives Papa a squirt in the eye.','Fjjw5LQ8VRtnkYX1bllIlzQkpgOS',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4918,192,'FjaUxYCkDUqLk9yiGDKCAObJFSZh','“I have a question,” says Sister Bear.\n“What is that tall thing over there?”\n“It’s the silo,” says Ben,\n“where we store the wheat that we sell to folks who make things to eat.”\n“Because wheat’s what it takes to make the flour that goes into bread, cookies, and cakes.”','FjQyACHKsP8wOqiD1kZ3npf_4ZdL',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4919,192,'FswB2j6W28b1wa-pRi66-Q294hPr','Says Mrs. Ben, “It’s lunchtime!\nPlease take your seats. \nEveryone sit down and have some eats!”\nAnd what a lunch it is!\nFarm-fresh foods of every kind.\nFor dessert, they munch watermelon down to the rind.','Fo1OusyIOMzO_l-Al4rwgQBn5YHi',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4920,192,'Fp-PHGRXgs7a7Du4XXl87qyCgN0o','But Brother has another question to ask.\n“We can see that farming’s a very big task.\nMy question is this: Is farming hard or is it fun?”\n“Hmm,” says Ben.\n“Is farming hard or is it fun?\nWell, it’s not a job for everyone.”','FvYkMDWXp_tc-6Cr_wSE4LCjSK3t',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4921,192,'FsRkmOgFESI3aUt89cBCviCLR_Uv','“There are hogs to slop,\nhorses to feed,','FgvTr8L9t0U35zBZA1ovCi14vdnG',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4922,192,'FiYlJKrv8a8VApGEZKXilF0q1U7F','fences to mend,\ngardens to weed,','FioCCzfXq469GpZEBZoFjX5QAyRy',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4923,192,'FuTHigDeYGA_OGYFKE4dBd_TQc1k','sheep to shear,\nfertilizer to spread.”','FmkAphV7Y4zhH0bNcc_gozoxT8Vu',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4924,192,'FjjvCDjG7dTX3PhTUjakTb96nS7Z','“But when the sun goes down and the sky is red-\nwhen the livestock are all bedded down and fed,\nand I sit on the porch with Mrs. Ben-”\n“Er, what was that question of yours again?”\n“Oh yes: Is farming hard or is it fun?”','Fp7wjp0yjW-aaKphe25_4nGApXON',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4925,192,'Fg0-uQS47P38AKnMCmY7Uhujqu2O','“Well, yes, it is hard, but we love it, son,\nso I guess you might say farming’s hard fun.”','FlxkSTulk0N9NgTg2JQTF5Ua7O87',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4926,192,'Fk2Fs0aEcD7wor88CB667io2gVdc','The Berenstain Bear Down on The Farm\n--by Stan & Jan Berenstain','Fl7eFSoz6c3eqGO0KIpV0F1NIbIG',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4927,192,'FqLvNTOhbx_3xMdqgZnwIFWjbyC8','“This way, please. We are on our way to visit our friend Farmer Ben today.”','Fh7GEkBJPdxSc5C-fEjTyuNiJXqZ',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4928,192,'Ft0Dfudn8AljW4CCoGVaxLyECUZV','“There’s Ben’s farm just up ahead.\nAs you can see, it is quite a spread.”','FufA2RY4sIsdax07ebHd_MH2LE_L',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4929,192,'Ft7B8-I0f2s3ZJ4Ssa4a7Ei3cPCp','“There’s Ben himself feeding his stock-\nand there’s Mrs. Ben feeding her flock.”\n“And there’s Big Red, the rooster, \nmaking much ado about his big, loud cock-a-doodle-doo.”','FiA_iMZDuYi4Q6s2PgAPO3q2PLiK',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4930,192,'Fq30gweG4KMCxCkaQyr8SbGjV079','“Your farm is so big,” says Ma.\n“as big as can be! It reaches as far as the eye can see.”\n“Yes, it’s a big ‘un!” says Ben.\n“A hundred acres- that’s ten times ten.”\n“We grow peas and beans, and corn and wheat,\nand all kinds of other good things to eat.”','FvU5La2LP2rt0U5gGre43U4hQi79',0,'2018-02-11 03:58:45','2018-02-11 03:58:45'),(4939,187,'FguzBOIDakw6lwEsjXdknKpABiBu','The Thing That Went Thump\n--by Maria Fleming','Ft8LlBqutB2XG_MpEzti7It70BK0',0,'2018-02-11 04:02:04','2018-02-11 04:02:04'),(4940,187,'FgigkKu1hfsfuoqCvkMhkyttt8