,'Long,long ago,dinosaurs lived everywhere,\nbut they were not alone.\nSmall, furry animals called mammals\nlived with the dinosaurs.\nThe mammals were different from the dinosaurs.','FvkvpJVOWglFH17TB17MHcp9M5BO',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6921,90,'FjDpMEQaKm8r99rXoBlzsgnKYAFg','The mammals were very small.\nInstead of scaly skin,the mammals had hair.\nMother mammals fed their babies milk.\nMother dinosaurs did not.\nDinosaurs and mammals lived together\nfor millions of years.\nThe dinosaurs grew bigger and bigger.\nBut the mammals stayed small.\nWhen the dinosaurs died, the mammals survived.\nMillions of years passed. The mammals grew larger.\nSome of these mammals looked like animals alive today.\nAnd some of these mammals looked very strange!','FgEs2jPodP9CAACS1PmGBjITBiC5',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6922,90,'FvcJx7CMy6pYnrHOrR5BHuyJqN_j','WOOLLYMAMMOTH\nYou say it like this:WOOL-ee MAM-uth\nWoolly mammoths looked like hairy elephants.\nThey lived where it was very cold.\nThey used their big tusks to dig\nunder the snow to get grass to eat.\nSometimes mammoths froze to death under the snow.\nIn very cold places, such asAlaska,\npeople sometimes find mammoths still frozen today.','FhsPAUHbiH4aLGjqTkV6zjfZVbpj',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6923,90,'Fhs8e6WThuBPFRn_phIqJcf3TEsn','SMILODON\nYou say it like this:SMILE-oh-don\nSmilodon is also called a “saber-toothedtiger.”\nIts teeth were as sharp as knives\nand longer than your hand.\nIt ate meat.It hid until an animal came close.\nThen it jumped on the animal-and ate it!','FvMsXgBkv3yqxDgLqENWNFTDzHhW',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6924,90,'Fr4o1bkzFd7g-nuDOST8cGpL-lfX','GLYPTODON\nYou say it like this:GLIP-toe-don\nThe Glyptondon was the size of a small car.\nIt was covered with bony skin from head to tail.\nSome glyptodons had a bonyclub at the end of their tails.\nThey were not fast, but they never\nhad to runaway from anything.','FvqGcH2gev8X1q3YDCjvzkPWyUyS',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6925,90,'Fhw6TYXJXym53Ch_RX0ej2iXr-6J','BASILOSAURUS\nYou say it like this:BASS-ill-oh-sawr-us\nBasilosaurus was an early whale.\nIt looked a little like a sea serpent.\nIt had along,thin body and lots of sharp teeth.It ate fish.','FgUfSy8mjNuzNp56K1Je9hLTmBQP',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6926,90,'Fimjl51CzB8LJDH9jArFVhCp2Gys','PLATYBELODON\nYou say it like this:plat-ee-BELL-oh-don\nPlatybelodon was as big as an elephant.\nIts front teeth were as big as shovels.\nThey were shaped like shovels too!\nPlatybelodon dug up plants\nto eat with its shovel-like teeth.','FgrpbArr94g7odusc2X0iWNkYl01',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6927,90,'FlXhg1cw_Z99SQ56kLAO7m4k9JIf','YRACOTHERIUM\nYou say it like this:Hi-RACK-oh-THEER-ee-um\nHyracotherium was the ancestor of all horses.\nBut it was much smaller than the horses of today.\nIt was the size of a small dog.\nIt was too small to run fast.\nIt was too small to protect itself.\nIt had to hide so it didn’t get eaten.','Fim_jh8FDt-4SBx7v2QjPq2gxM6v',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6928,90,'Fhiw3_ArLPOgBgyAFyJ9v2mMCCuV','ANDREWSARCHUS\nYou say it like this:an-droo-SARK-us\nAndrewsarchus had jaws that were longer than your arm.\nIt had lots of strong teeth.\nAndrewsarchus ate other animals.\nIt ate all the meat,then it crushed\nthe bones and ate them,too!','FmrV-l2OAd9zWeZ5sAOi--rnAEdR',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6929,90,'FrPmi4SFR6nWJrNvBA-Db1_rZ56L','MEGATHERIUM\nYou say it like this:meg-ah-THEER-ee-um\nMegatherium looked like a bear with a big,\nfat tail and very long claws.\nBut it was much,much bigger than any bear.\nMegatherium was as tall as the treetops\nwhen it stood on its back legs.\nIt ripped down high branches to eat the leaves.','FpSRio9Fpo0hk5-brRTwRdoIjZ3A',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6930,90,'FqaOvfiCVqZJP968bPIG58B-bPv1','MACRAUCHENIA\nYou say it like this: mak-raw-KEEN-ee-ah\nThe Macrauchenia looked like\nthree animals mixed together.\nIt had a body like a camel.\nIt had feet like a rhinoceros.\nIt had a short trunk,like an elephant.\nAll of this put together made one strange beast!','Fioyv_w2MgQnj8FSl8qeeeiWJFv4',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6931,90,'FsCiq5ayzml-RG86k3RSSTYICLvZ','INDRICOTHERIUM\nYou say it like this: in-DRIK-oh-THEER-ee-um\nIndricotherium was the largest land mammal ever.\nIt weighed more than four elephants put together.\nIf Indricotherium was still alive today，\nit could peek into a second-story window\nwithout stretching. Now that is really big!','FjEK11nYrDrTECHdJmMvIeAcIU1n',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6932,90,'FtmHR_w4iRG0caigoeoXXqJ-lD8Z','HOMOSAPIEN\nYou say it like this:HO-mo SAPE-ee-in\nHomo sapiens is another way to say”people.”\nEarly people gathered plants and hunted animals to eat.\nSometimes they painted the animals\nthey hunted on the walls of caves.\nWe can still see these paintings today.','Fg-3Wjyadt7Vq_t4QAg52Pf7lRfK',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6933,90,'Fq4Li2xU4zcdxOzKmp-akmabRqQJ','Now people live all over the earth.\nBut the other mammals in this book are gone.\nThey died long ago.\nSometimes when they died\ntheir bones were preserved.\nThese bones are called fossils.\nScientists study fossil bones to learn about\nancient mammals and other prehistoric animals.','Fh4WDmJQwa9B1sCdFqenS6mKgoPQ',0,'2018-03-08 09:38:53','2018-03-08 09:38:53'),(6934,87,'Fi7OiD9BL8p-EgEBvCm3nGHgx6VW','To The Rescue','FjJadA0sCKMz06PjYUyenfjSt1c3',0,'2018-03-08 09:44:13','2018-03-08 09:44:13'),(6935,87,'Fh5XHdeNrYOHRmx3cBCrJ8K2d9ax','Dad goes to the basement.\nHe has work to do.\nI am working, too.\nI am working with my tool.','FrLfM3Uj6tsV_hfIVdtbbwhbJ8wC',0,'2018-03-08 09:44:13','2018-03-08 09:44:13'),(6936,87,'FtmrRNGobcbqS3BUcKw8THJB8QNy','I am tired of working.\nI hear my dad walking up the basement stairs.\nHe calls me.\nHe need